Descriptives

Distribution of readings

The maximum value in the color disc is 3.5, and in the colorimeter its 2.2. When readings exceed 2.2, the colorimeter threw an error. These observations are replaced with 2.4.

Spotchecks

COMMENTS

  • chlorine test steps followed in c90% of cases in Malawi, with higher scores for color disc
  • chlorine test steps followed in almost 100% of cases in Uganda, but much smaller sample
  • readings for colorwheel are similar (not statistically different); indeed, on average the main enumerators reading is higher than the checkers (exception: TCR in Uganda)
